cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.MM

The paper deals with sparse approximations for image processing applications, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning the hierarchical structure of over-complete dictionaries, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The method also involves nearest neighbor matching, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the experiments involve image denoising/superresolution and compressive video/light-field sensing, which are topics in multimedia (cs.MM).
